- She's not going to Auschwitz.

1402
02:25:55,547 --> 02:25:59,968
I'd never do that to her. No, I want her
to come back to Vienna with me.

1403
02:26:00,052 --> 02:26:03,096
I want her to come
to work for me there.

1404
02:26:03,180 --> 02:26:07,684
- I want to grow old with her.
- Are you mad?

1405
02:26:07,768 --> 02:26:14,066
- Amon, you can't take her to Vienna with you.
- No, of course I can't.

1406
02:26:14,483 --> 02:26:17,069
That's what I'd like to do.

1407
02:26:17,152 --> 02:26:23,116
What I can do, if I'm any sort of a man,
is the next most merciful thing.

1408
02:26:23,200 --> 02:26:28,205
I shall take her into the woods and shoot
her painlessly in the back of the head.

1409
02:26:37,339 --> 02:26:41,760
What was it you said
for a natural 21?

1410
02:26:41,927 --> 02:26:44,304
Was it 14,800?

1411
02:26:44,388 --> 02:26:47,808
<i>Jews of Schindler, to these tables!
Say your names clearly.</i>

1412
02:26:47,891 --> 02:26:51,270
- We are the family Dresner.
-Juda, Jonas...

1413
02:26:51,353 --> 02:26:53,689
...Donata and Chaja.

1414
02:26:53,772 --> 02:26:57,442
- We are Rosners. Henry, Manci...
- And Leo.

1415
02:26:57,526 --> 02:27:00,904
- And our son.
- I am Olek.

1416
02:27:00,988 --> 02:27:02,489
Maria Mischel.

1417
02:27:02,573 --> 02:27:05,409
Chaim Nowak.

1418
02:27:05,534 --> 02:27:07,870
Wulkan, Markus.

1419
02:27:07,953 --> 02:27:10,330
Michael Lemper.

1420
02:27:11,206 --> 02:27:13,375
Itzhak Stern.

1421
02:27:13,667 --> 02:27:16,712
Rebeka and Joseph Bau.

1422
02:27:17,254 --> 02:27:19,548
- Rosalia Nussbaum.
- Wilhelm Nussbaum.

1423
02:27:20,007 --> 02:27:22,426
Jakob Levartov.

1424
02:27:23,010 --> 02:27:25,762
- Farber, Rosa.
- Farber, Andrzej.

1425
02:27:25,846 --> 02:27:28,640
- Sara.
- Friehof, Fischel.

1426
02:27:29,975 --> 02:27:31,852
Mietek Pemper.

1427
02:27:31,935 --> 02:27:34,438
Poldek and Mila Pfefferberg.

1428
02:27:34,521 --> 02:27:37,024
Horowitz, Dolek.

1429
02:27:38,233 --> 02:27:40,194
Adam Levy.

1430
02:27:40,277 --> 02:27:42,529
Marcel Goldberg.

1431
02:27:42,613 --> 02:27:46,074
Klipstein, Isak David.

1432
02:27:46,158 --> 02:27:48,076
Altmann, Eduard.

1433
02:27:48,160 --> 02:27:50,245
Grunberg, Miriam.

1434
02:27:50,329 --> 02:27:52,414
Luftig, Eliasz.

1435
02:27:52,497 --> 02:27:54,541
Hilmann, Eduard.

1436
02:27:54,625 --> 02:27:56,877
Erna Rothberg.

1437
02:27:57,085 --> 02:28:00,005
Zuckermann, Jetti.

1438
02:28:00,297 --> 02:28:03,050
Helen Hirsch.

1439
02:28:04,134 --> 02:28:07,262
The worst is over.

1440
02:28:07,763 --> 02:28:11,892
<i>Men to this transport
and women to this transport.</i>

1441
02:28:11,975 --> 02:28:16,855
<i>Be careful! Men to this transport
and women to this transport.</i>

1442
02:28:16,939 --> 02:28:21,443
<i>Watch your step! Men to this transport
and women to this transport.</i>

1443
02:28:59,439 --> 02:29:03,986
Wonderful Olek, wonderful.

1444
02:29:04,027 --> 02:29:08,824
You know how we make
ice into water?

1445
02:29:09,491 --> 02:29:11,785
Olek, get another one!

1446
02:29:50,073 --> 02:29:53,285
<i>Position yourselves
all in a single row!</i>

1447
02:29:53,493 --> 02:29:58,332
You'll be pleased with the level
of efficiency I get from these workers.

1448
02:29:59,666 --> 02:30:01,835
Budzyn, under my command...

1449
02:30:01,919 --> 02:30:04,838
...was the envy of every other commandant
in the labour camp system.

1450
02:30:04,880 --> 02:30:06,423
- The prisoners, however...
- Excuse me!

1451
02:30:06,465 --> 02:30:09,676
...they would have rather been
somewhere else.

1452
02:30:23,690 --> 02:30:26,985
The train with the women
has already left Plaszow...

1453
02:30:27,069 --> 02:30:30,822
...and will be arriving
here very shortly.

1454
02:30:30,948 --> 02:30:33,659
I know you've had
a long journey.

1455
02:30:33,700 --> 02:30:36,995
But it's only a short walk
further to the factory...

1456
02:30:37,079 --> 02:30:42,501
...where hot soup and bread
is waiting for you.

1457
02:30:42,584 --> 02:30:45,170
Welcome to Brinnlitz!

1458
02:30:54,596 --> 02:30:57,641
- Beans in chunt?
- Beans are the best part.

1459
02:30:57,683 --> 02:30:59,935
I don't like beans.

1460
02:31:00,018 --> 02:31:03,939
Beans and meat
and potatoes and bread.

1461
02:31:04,022 --> 02:31:06,900
That's not the way
you make chunt.

1462
02:31:10,654 --> 02:31:13,907
- Eggs in chunt?
- Yes!

1463
02:31:16,076 --> 02:31:18,954
- I don't like chunt.
- No, you don't.

1464
02:31:18,996 --> 02:31:24,126
- What do you like?
- I like caviar!

1465
02:31:24,209 --> 02:31:25,627
One day on the fire...

1466
02:31:25,627 --> 02:31:27,713
-Oh, yes!
-One day...

1467
02:32:32,945 --> 02:32:34,821
Position yourselves
in front of the wagons!

1468
02:32:36,406 --> 02:32:39,743
You've got to stay together.

1469
02:32:39,826 --> 02:32:44,122
Leave the wagons!
Leave the wagons!

1470
02:32:45,040 --> 02:32:47,376
I said, leave the wagons!

1471
02:32:48,752 --> 02:32:51,171
<i>Bagaze zostawic!</i>

1472
02:32:53,507 --> 02:32:55,592
<i>Faster! Quick! Quick!</i>

1473
02:32:55,676 --> 02:32:57,928
<i>What's going on back there?</i>

1474
02:33:00,514 --> 02:33:02,432
Move it!

1475
02:33:07,229 --> 02:33:11,108
Come on, out!
Hurry up, out!

1476
02:33:11,149 --> 02:33:17,406
Thirty, thirty-five,
forty, forty-five...

1477
02:33:17,489 --> 02:33:19,408
<i>Out!</i>

1478
02:33:19,491 --> 02:33:21,910
<i>Get out!</i>

1479
02:33:21,994 --> 02:33:24,872
<i>Quicker, get out!</i>

1480
02:33:28,625 --> 02:33:31,253
<i>All of you, out!</i>

1481
02:33:32,171 --> 02:33:35,924
- Where are the list makers?
- Where are the tables?

1482
02:33:38,844 --> 02:33:40,512
<i>Move the line!</i>

1483
02:33:41,013 --> 02:33:43,015
<i>Get out!</i>

1484
02:33:47,728 --> 02:33:51,148
<i>- Quick! Get out!
- Faster!</i>

1485
02:33:53,734 --> 02:33:55,777
<i>Quicker!</i>

1486
02:33:55,819 --> 02:33:58,155
<i>Come on, be quick!</i>

1487
02:33:58,238 --> 02:34:01,742
Mama, where are we?

1488
02:34:02,326 --> 02:34:05,537
- 17, 18, 20-
- They're in Auschwitz.

1489
02:34:05,621 --> 02:34:09,541
The train was never routed here.
A paperwork mistake.

1490
02:34:17,883 --> 02:34:20,344
<i>Take off your shoes!</i>

1491
02:34:33,273 --> 02:34:36,193
<i>Quicker, quicker!</i>

1492
02:34:39,571 --> 02:34:41,073
<i>Take off your clothes!
Hurry up!</i>

1493
02:34:41,198 --> 02:34:43,867
<i>Hurry up! Stay in a row
and take off your clothes!</i>

1494
02:34:45,410 --> 02:34:47,079
<i>Quicker!</i>

1495
02:35:01,844 --> 02:35:04,805
<i>Quicker!</i>

1496
02:35:04,888 --> 02:35:08,183
<i>Take off your clothes quickly!
Hurry up!</i>

1497
02:35:11,937 --> 02:35:14,022
SHOWERS AND DISINFECTION

1498
02:35:15,315 --> 02:35:17,276
<i>Go in, hurry up!</i>

1499
02:35:20,279 --> 02:35:21,738
Quicker!

1500
02:35:21,864 --> 02:35:24,616
<i>Go to the showers, quickly!</i>

1501
02:35:26,702 --> 02:35:30,956
<i>Quicker! Quicker!</i>

1502
02:38:01,106 --> 02:38:03,025
Eyes on the necks!

1503
02:38:05,736 --> 02:38:08,488
Hands on the shoulders!

1504
02:38:08,572 --> 02:38:11,783
<i>- How old are you, mother?
- Sixty-eight.</i>

1505
02:38:11,825 --> 02:38:17,331
- Cough for me, mother.
- They say to fall against the fence is a kindness.

1506
02:38:17,623 --> 02:38:20,125
Don't kill yourself
against the fence, Clara.

1507
02:38:20,209 --> 02:38:24,046
If you do, you'll never
know what happened to you.

1508
02:38:25,923 --> 02:38:28,467
- How old are you, mother?
- Sixty-six, sir.

1509
02:38:28,550 --> 02:38:30,761
- Sir?
- Good morning.

1510
02:38:30,844 --> 02:38:33,805
A mistake has been made.
We are not supposed to be here.

1511
02:38:33,889 --> 02:38:37,601
We work for Oskar Schindler.
We are Schindler Jews.

1512
02:38:37,684 --> 02:38:41,188
- Who is Oskar Schindler?
- He had a factory in Krakow.

1513
02:38:41,271 --> 02:38:45,651
- Enamelware.
- A pot maker.

1514
02:38:46,109 --> 02:38:48,320
How old are you, mother?

1515
02:38:52,533 --> 02:38:58,330
You are not the only industrialist
who needs labour...

1516
02:38:58,539 --> 02:39:00,832
...Mr. Schindler.

1517
02:39:00,916 --> 02:39:03,752
I remember earlier this year,
IG-Color ordered...

1518
02:39:03,836 --> 02:39:09,675
...a trainload of Hungarians
for its chemical factory.

1519
02:39:09,758 --> 02:39:13,679
The train came in
through the archway...

1520
02:39:13,762 --> 02:39:19,393
...and the officer in charge
of the selection went immediately to work...

1521
02:39:19,476 --> 02:39:22,187
...and sent 2,000 of them...

1522
02:39:22,229 --> 02:39:25,816
...straight away
to "special treatment".

1523
02:39:26,525 --> 02:39:32,114
It is not my task to interfere with
the processes that take place down here.

1524
02:39:33,240 --> 02:39:38,370
Why do you think I can help you
if I can't help IG-Color?

1525
02:39:38,453 --> 02:39:41,748
Allow me to express the reason.

1526
02:39:50,215 --> 02:39:53,719
I'm not making
any judgement about you.

1527
02:39:53,719 --> 02:39:56,305
It's just that I know
that in the coming months...

1528
02:39:56,346 --> 02:40:00,142
...we're all going
to need portable wealth.

1529
02:40:02,769 --> 02:40:05,480
I could have you arrested.

1530
02:40:05,564 --> 02:40:10,861
I'm protected by powerful friends.
You should know that.

1531
02:40:13,238 --> 02:40:17,159
I do not say
I am accepting them.

1532
02:40:17,242 --> 02:40:22,539
All I say is, I'm not comfortable
with them on the table.

1533
02:40:36,094 --> 02:40:39,306
I have a shipment
coming in tomorrow.

1534
02:40:39,389 --> 02:40:41,767
I'll cut you 300 units from it.

1535
02:40:41,850 --> 02:40:45,771
New ones.
These are fresh.

1536
02:40:49,525 --> 02:40:53,529
- The train comes, we turn it around.
- Yes, yes, yes!

1537
02:40:53,612 --> 02:40:55,155
- It's yours.
- I understand.

1538
02:40:55,531 --> 02:40:58,283
I want these.

1539
02:41:00,827 --> 02:41:04,498
You shouldn't
get stuck on names.

1540
02:41:11,255 --> 02:41:15,509
That's right.
It creates a lot of paperwork.

1541
02:41:15,592 --> 02:41:19,596
Zoldinger, Ernestina!
Waldergrun, Hilda!

1542
02:41:19,680 --> 02:41:21,890
Waldergrun, Leonora!

1543
02:41:21,974 --> 02:41:25,352
Laast, Anna!
Pfefferberg, Mila!

1544
02:41:25,394 --> 02:41:28,981
Dresner, Ruth!
Dresner, Danka!

1545
02:41:29,064 --> 02:41:32,776
Nussbaum, Sidonia!
Rosner, Manci!

1546
02:41:32,860 --> 02:41:38,866
Hirsch, Helen! Grosz, Chaja Sara!
Seelenfreund, Estella!

1547
02:41:53,714 --> 02:41:55,883
<i>Move it!
Move it, quick!</i>

1548
02:41:55,966 --> 02:42:00,512
<i>- Faster! Faster!
-Come on!</i>

1549
02:42:02,139 --> 02:42:05,017
<i>Quick, quick!
Faster!</i>

1550
02:42:06,935 --> 02:42:11,023
<i>- Faster!
-Hurry up!</i>

1551
02:42:19,323 --> 02:42:22,409
No! No! No!

1552
02:42:36,757 --> 02:42:40,469
No! No! No!

1553
02:42:44,181 --> 02:42:46,475
No! No! No!

1554
02:42:48,560 --> 02:42:52,523
Hey! Hey! Hey!
What are you doing?

1555
02:42:52,606 --> 02:42:57,402
These are mine! These are my workers!
They should be on my train!

1556
02:42:57,528 --> 02:43:00,155
They're skilled munitions workers!
They're essential!

1557
02:43:00,864 --> 02:43:03,408
Essential girls!

1558
02:43:05,577 --> 02:43:09,998
Their fingers polish the insides
of shell metal casings.

1559
02:43:10,082 --> 02:43:13,502
How else am I to polish the inside of
a 45 millimetre shell casing?

1560
02:43:13,585 --> 02:43:17,422
You tell me.
You tell me!

1561
02:43:18,841 --> 02:43:23,011
Back on the train!
Back on the train!

1562
02:45:17,292 --> 02:45:21,547
Under Department "W" provisions...

1563
02:45:21,630 --> 02:45:26,009
...it is unlawful
to kill a worker without just cause.

1564
02:45:26,093 --> 02:45:29,096
Under the Businesses
Compensation Fund...

1565
02:45:29,179 --> 02:45:33,475
...I am entitled to file
damage claims for such deaths.

1566
02:45:33,559 --> 02:45:36,520
If you shoot without thinking...

1567
02:45:36,603 --> 02:45:40,858
...you go to prison, I get paid.

1568
02:45:40,941 --> 02:45:43,277
That's how it works.

1569
02:45:43,360 --> 02:45:48,532
So, there will be no
summary executions here.

1570
02:45:49,283 --> 02:45:54,079
There will be no interference
of any kind with production.

1571
02:45:54,162 --> 02:45:59,293
In hopes of ensuring that, guards will
no longer be allowed on the factory floor...

1572
02:45:59,376 --> 02:46:03,046
...without my authorization.

1573
02:46:07,843 --> 02:46:12,598
For your cooperation,
you have my gratitude.

1574
02:46:13,223 --> 02:46:15,350
Come on, come!

1575
02:46:15,976 --> 02:46:18,061
<i>Oh, boy! I haven't seen
something like that since years.</i>

1576
02:46:18,145 --> 02:46:21,023
Come on, boys, come!

1577
02:46:46,715 --> 02:46:52,638
No doorman or maitre d'
will ever mistake you again...

1578
02:46:52,721 --> 02:46:55,057
...I promise.

1579
02:47:01,772 --> 02:47:05,526
- This is Itzhak Stern, my accountant.
- You must be Mrs. Schindler.

1580
02:47:05,567 --> 02:47:08,237
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Emilie has volunteered to work in the clinic.

1581
02:47:08,278 --> 02:47:10,239
- Very generous of you.
- I know.

1582
02:47:10,280 --> 02:47:12,950
We need to talk
when you have a moment.

1583
02:47:13,033 --> 02:47:15,619
This is my wife, Stern.
I don't keep any secrets from my spouse.

1584
02:47:15,702 --> 02:47:18,705
Oskar, please, attend to business.
It's much more attractive.

1585
02:47:18,789 --> 02:47:19,706
- Madam.
- Hello!

1586
02:47:19,748 --> 02:47:20,666
What is it?

1587
02:47:20,707 --> 02:47:23,502
We've received an angry complaint
from the Armaments Board.

1588
02:47:23,585 --> 02:47:25,754
The artillery shells,
tank shells, rocket casings!

1589
02:47:25,838 --> 02:47:28,507
Apparently all of them
have failed quality control tests.

1590
02:47:28,507 --> 02:47:29,550
That's to be expected!

1591
02:47:29,633 --> 02:47:32,845
Start-up problems. This isn't pots
and pans. This is a precise business.

1592
02:47:32,928 --> 02:47:34,888
- I'll write them a letter.
- They're withholding payment.

1593
02:47:34,930 --> 02:47:39,101
Sure, so would I, so would you. I wouldn't
worry. We'll get it right one of these days.

1594
02:47:39,142 --> 02:47:43,605
There's a rumour you've been going
around miscalibrating the machines.

1595
02:47:43,647 --> 02:47:48,402
They could shut us down,
send us back to Auschwitz.

1596
02:47:49,528 --> 02:47:51,905
I'll call around, find out
where we can buy shells.

1597
02:47:51,989 --> 02:47:54,074
- Pass them off as ours.
- I don't see the difference...

1598
02:47:54,074 --> 02:47:55,117
...whether they're made here
or somewhere else.

1599
02:47:55,200 --> 02:47:56,618
You don't see a difference?
I see a difference.

1600
02:47:56,618 --> 02:47:57,995
You'll lose a lot of money.

1601
02:47:58,078 --> 02:48:01,373
Fewer shells will be made.
Stern, if this factory ever produces...

1602
02:48:01,456 --> 02:48:06,837
...a shell that can actually be fired,
I'll be very unhappy.

1603
02:48:06,920 --> 02:48:09,965
- Hello, madam.
- How do you do?

1604
02:48:23,395 --> 02:48:27,941
How are you doing, Rabbi?
Rabbi!

1605
02:48:30,110 --> 02:48:32,863
Good, Mr. Director.

1606
02:48:34,031 --> 02:48:36,283
Sun's going down.

1607
02:48:38,535 --> 02:48:40,621
Yes, it is.

1608
02:48:41,872 --> 02:48:45,959
What day is this? Friday?
It is Friday, isn't it?

1609
02:48:46,043 --> 02:48:48,003
Is it?

1610
02:48:51,465 --> 02:48:56,470
What's the matter with you?
You should be preparing for the Sabbath.

1611
02:48:56,553 --> 02:48:59,389
Shouldn't you?

1612
02:49:05,395 --> 02:49:10,526
I've got some wine.
In my office. Come!

1613
02:50:25,184 --> 02:50:28,270
<i>What?</i>

1614
02:50:28,353 --> 02:50:33,275
Do you have any money,
uh, hidden away someplace...

1615
02:50:33,358 --> 02:50:36,528
...that I don't know about?

1616
02:50:39,489 --> 02:50:41,992
No!

1617
02:50:46,288 --> 02:50:50,334
Why?
Am I broke?

1618
02:50:53,295 --> 02:50:55,464
Well...

1619
02:50:56,381 --> 02:51:02,763
<i>Yesterday morning, at 2:41 a. m...</i>

1620
02:51:02,846 --> 02:51:06,808
<i>...at General Eisenhower's
headquarters...</i>

1621
02:51:06,892 --> 02:51:09,561
<i>...General Jodl...</i>

1622
02:51:09,686 --> 02:51:13,774
<i>...signed the Act
of Unconditional Surrender...</i>

1623
02:51:13,857 --> 02:51:19,905
<i>...of all German land,
sea and air forces in Europe...</i>

1624
02:51:19,988 --> 02:51:24,076
<i>...to the Allied
Expeditionary Force.</i>

1625
02:51:24,076 --> 02:51:28,247
<i>And simultaneously
to the Soviet High Command.</i>

1626
02:51:28,997 --> 02:51:32,793
<i>The German war is,
therefore, at an end.</i>

1627
02:51:32,876 --> 02:51:34,878
<i>But let us not forget for a moment...</i>

1628
02:51:34,920 --> 02:51:39,216
I think it's time the guards
came into the factory.

1629
02:51:39,299 --> 02:51:42,469
<i>...Japan, with all
her treachery and greed...</i>

1630
02:51:42,553 --> 02:51:48,058
The unconditional surrender
of Germany has just been announced.

1631
02:51:48,141 --> 02:51:52,771
At midnight tonight,
the war is over.

1632
02:51:54,690 --> 02:51:57,067
Tomorrow you'll
begin the process...

1633
02:51:57,150 --> 02:52:00,863
...of looking for survivors
of your families.

1634
02:52:03,323 --> 02:52:08,787
In most cases,
you won't find them.

1635
02:52:09,955 --> 02:52:12,791
After six long years
of murder...

1636
02:52:12,916 --> 02:52:18,213
...victims are being mourned
throughout the world.

1637
02:52:18,297 --> 02:52:21,425
We've survived.

1638
02:52:21,508 --> 02:52:25,762
Many of you have come up
to me and thanked me.

1639
02:52:27,764 --> 02:52:29,933
Thank yourselves.

1640
02:52:31,059 --> 02:52:34,438
Thank your fearless Stern...

1641
02:52:34,479 --> 02:52:36,857
...and others among you
who worried about you...

1642
02:52:36,899 --> 02:52:40,944
...and faced death
at every moment.

1643
02:52:43,864 --> 02:52:46,533
I'm a member of the Nazi party.

1644
02:52:46,658 --> 02:52:49,912
I'm a munitions manufacturer.

1645
02:52:49,995 --> 02:52:52,414
I'm a profiteer of slave labour.

1646
02:52:52,497 --> 02:52:56,210
I am a criminal.

1647
02:52:56,293 --> 02:53:01,298
At midnight you'll be free,
and I'll be hunted.

1648
02:53:01,924 --> 02:53:05,427
I shall remain with you until
five minutes after midnight...

1649
02:53:05,511 --> 02:53:11,767
...after which time,
and I hope you'll forgive me I have to flee.

1650
02:53:13,894 --> 02:53:17,648
I know you have received orders
from our commandant...

1651
02:53:17,731 --> 02:53:22,778
...which he has received from his superiors
to dispose of the population of this camp.

1652
02:53:22,861 --> 02:53:25,280
Now would be
the time to do it.

1653
02:53:25,364 --> 02:53:31,328
Here they are, they're all here.
This is your opportunity.

1654
02:53:35,457 --> 02:53:39,169
Or you could leave...

1655
02:53:39,253 --> 02:53:41,547
...and return
to your families as men...

1656
02:53:41,630 --> 02:53:45,551
...instead of murderers.

1657
02:54:25,716 --> 02:54:29,887
In memory of the countless
victims among your people...

1658
02:54:29,970 --> 02:54:34,183
...I ask us to observe
three minutes of silence.

1659
02:55:28,862 --> 02:55:34,076
- Thank you, Mr. Jereth.
- Thank you, Mr. Jereth.

1660
02:55:34,159 --> 02:55:36,495
Open wide.

1661
02:55:38,205 --> 02:55:40,290
Thank you, Mr. Jereth.

1662
02:55:58,851 --> 02:56:01,144
Thank you, Mr. Jereth!

1663
02:56:25,169 --> 02:56:29,464
As soon as peace occurs,
I want...

1664
02:56:29,548 --> 02:56:33,677
...um, I want that cloth
distributed to the workers.

1665
02:56:33,719 --> 02:56:36,305
Two and a half metres each.

1666
02:56:36,388 --> 02:56:39,600
Also, each person is
to get a bottle of vodka.

1667
02:56:39,683 --> 02:56:42,686
They won't drink it.
They know its value.

1668
02:56:42,769 --> 02:56:46,273
Likewise those Egipshi cigarettes
we organized.

1669
02:56:46,356 --> 02:56:50,569
It'll be done.
Everything you ask.

1670
02:57:09,713 --> 02:57:13,967
We've written a letter,
trying to explain things...

1671
02:57:14,051 --> 02:57:17,221
...in case you are captured.

1672
02:57:18,514 --> 02:57:21,725
Every worker has signed it.

1673
02:57:31,777 --> 02:57:33,695
Thank you!

1674
02:58:00,514 --> 02:58:02,850
It is Hebrew, from the Talmud.

1675
02:58:02,933 --> 02:58:08,981
It says:
"Whoever saves one life, saves the world entire. "

1676
02:58:47,895 --> 02:58:51,398
I could have got more out.

1677
02:58:52,566 --> 02:58:55,068
I could have got more.
I don't know.

1678
02:58:55,652 --> 02:58:57,487
If I just...

1679
02:58:58,614 --> 02:58:59,698
I could have got more.

1680
02:58:59,781 --> 02:59:05,287
Oskar, there are 1,100 people who are
alive because of you. Look at them.

1681
02:59:05,662 --> 02:59:08,165
If I'd made more money...

1682
02:59:12,169 --> 02:59:17,007
I threw away so much money.

1683
02:59:18,967 --> 02:59:21,970
You have no idea.

1684
02:59:22,054 --> 02:59:23,055
If I had just...

1685
02:59:23,138 --> 02:59:27,351
There will be generations
because of what you did.

1686
02:59:28,560 --> 02:59:30,938
I didn't do enough.

1687
02:59:31,021 --> 02:59:33,982
You did so much.

1688
02:59:37,402 --> 02:59:39,863
This car...

1689
02:59:39,947 --> 02:59:41,698
...Goeth would've bought this car.

1690
02:59:42,199 --> 02:59:46,954
Why did I keep the car?
Ten people right there.

1691
02:59:49,373 --> 02:59:52,292
Ten people.

1692
02:59:53,001 --> 02:59:55,796
Ten more people.

1693
02:59:57,631 --> 02:59:59,174
This pin...

1694
02:59:59,258 --> 03:00:03,011
...two people.

1695
03:00:03,720 --> 03:00:05,472
This is gold.

1696
03:00:05,556 --> 03:00:07,182
Two more people.

1697
03:00:07,558 --> 03:00:10,435
He would have given me
two for it, at least one.

1698
03:00:10,477 --> 03:00:13,856
He would have given me one,
one more.

1699
03:00:16,358 --> 03:00:19,111
One more person.

1700
03:00:20,779 --> 03:00:26,159
A person, Stern,
for this!

1701
03:00:28,120 --> 03:00:32,040
I could have gotten...

1702
03:00:32,124 --> 03:00:36,920
...one more person and I didn't.

1703
03:00:37,421 --> 03:00:40,883
And I, I didn't!

1704
03:02:09,346 --> 03:02:12,140
You have been liberated...

1705
03:02:12,224 --> 03:02:15,519
...by the Soviet Army!

1706
03:02:22,943 --> 03:02:24,611
Have you been in Poland?

1707
03:02:24,695 --> 03:02:28,198
I just came from Poland.

1708
03:02:29,408 --> 03:02:32,119
Are there any Jews left?

1709
03:02:37,207 --> 03:02:39,751
Where should we go?

1710
03:02:39,835 --> 03:02:41,920
Don't go east, that's for sure.

1711
03:02:42,004 --> 03:02:45,215
They hate you there.

1712
03:02:45,591 --> 03:02:49,469
I wouldn't go west either,
if I were you.

1713
03:02:50,387 --> 03:02:53,515
We could use some food.

1714
03:02:55,142 --> 03:02:59,229
Isn't there a town over there?

1715
03:04:12,052 --> 03:04:14,805
Long live, Hitler!